solutions.content:
If length of wordlist is smaller than 10, then smply guess all the word in wordlist.
If length of wordlist is bigger than 10, then..

First we random choose a word in wordlist, and guess it with master.
Here we might have 3 cases
1. None of the char is matched to secret.
2. Jackpot! All chars are matched
3. Only some chars are matched.

For the case 1, which might be the most helpful one.
Since we knew this word has zero match with secret word.
We loop through the original wordlist, and if there are words with any char match with this zero matched word. Then it must not the answer.
So we only keep words which also have zero match with this zero matched word.

For the cast 3, we knew that this word has some match with the secret word.
Let's say this word has PositiveNum match with secret word.
Since we already know it has "PositiveNum" match with secret word, so there must be PostivieNum of its chars is right.
So we only keep words with differences with this word less than/equal to 6-PositiveNum.

Well,  to be honest, this solution can't cover all the cases. For example, the secret word is "abcdef"
(Although I don't think 10 guesses is possibly enough for all the cases)
And if the wordlist is [abcdef, bbcdef, cbcdef, dbcdef, ebcdef, fbcdef, gbcdef, hbcdef........zbcdef]
Then this solution only have 10/26 = 38% chance to guess the secret word.
```
class Solution {
public:
    void findSecretWord(vector<string>& wordlist, Master& master) {
        if(wordlist.size()<=10){
            for(auto &str : wordlist){
                master.guess(str);
            }
        }else{
            for(int i=0; i<10; ++i){
                int n = wordlist.size();
                int randNum = rand() % n;
                string guessString = wordlist[randNum];
                int positiveNum = master.guess(guessString); 

                if(positiveNum == 6){ break; }
                else if(positiveNum == 0){ allNegClean(guessString, wordlist); }
                else{ positiveClean(guessString, wordlist, positiveNum); }
            }
        }
    }

private:
    void allNegClean(string &word, vector<string>& wordlist){
        vector<string> newList;
        for(int i=0; i<wordlist.size(); ++i){
            int j=0;
            for(; j<6; ++j){
                if(wordlist[i][j] == word[j]){ break; }
            }
            if(j==6){ newList.push_back(wordlist[i]); }
        }
        wordlist = newList;
    }

    void positiveClean(string &word, vector<string>& wordlist, int positiveNum){
        vector<string> newList;
        for(int i=0; i<wordlist.size(); ++i){
            int diff = 0;
            for(int j=0; j<6; ++j){
                if(wordlist[i][j] != word[j]){ diff++; }
            }
            if(diff<= 6-positiveNum && wordlist[i] != word){ newList.push_back(wordlist[i]); }
        }
        wordlist = newList;
    }
};
