```
2. Pruning. #1 does not even use the number of matches returned from guess. We can use it to prune the wordlist.
```
	public void findSecretWord(String[] wordlist, Master master) {
        int n=wordlist.length;
        boolean[] excl=new boolean[n]; 
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++) {
            if(excl[i]) continue;
            int match=master.guess(wordlist[i]);
            for(int j=i+1;j<n;j++) {
                if(matches(wordlist[i],wordlist[j])!=match) 
                    excl[j]=true;
            }
        }
    }
    private int matches(String s1, String s2) {
        int match=0;
        for(int i=0;i<s1.length();i++)
            if(s1.charAt(i)==s2.charAt(i))
                match++;
        return match;
    }
```
3. Math. In #2, we always pick the first un-deleted word to guess. For two random words, the probability that they have 0 matches is (25/26)^6 = 79%. So we get 0 from guess most of the time and the guess word has 0 matches with most words. This means we only eleminate few words after each guess. No matter how we pick the word, guess will always return 0. Thus we can pick a word that has the fewest zero matches with the list so that we can filter max number of words.
```
	private int LEN = 6;
    public void findSecretWord(String[] wordlist, Master master) {
        int matches = 0;
        List<String> words = Arrays.asList(wordlist);
        while(matches !=LEN) {
            String guess = pickWord(words);
            matches = master.guess(guess);
            if(matches == LEN) {
                return;
            }
            words = elimination(matches, guess, words);
        }
    }
    private String pickWord(List<String> words) {
        int n = words.size(), max=0, index=0;
        int[] count = new int[n];
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++) {
            String si = words.get(i);
            for(int j=i+1;j<n;j++) {
                if(matches(si, words.get(j))>0) {
                    count[i]++;
                    count[j]++;
                }
            }
            if(count[i]>max) {
                max = count[i];
                index = i;
            }
        }
        return words.get(index);
    }
    private List<String> elimination(int matches, String guess, List<String> words) {
        List<String> pruned = new ArrayList<>();
        for(String word:words) {
            if(matches(word, guess)==matches) {
                pruned.add(word);
            }    
        }
        return pruned;
    }
