1) My solution - just from the formula we've learned at school:
	**y = ax + b** => **b =y - ax**
	**b = y0 - ax0**
	**b = y1 - ax1**
	=> **y0 - ax0 = y1 - ax1**
	=> **a = (y0 - y1) / (x0 - x1)**
	then **b = y - ax**
	But if **x0 == x1** (it might be **x = const** for any **y**) we'll get devide by zero exception.
	So I just fixed it with **point.x == x0** condition for any point if **x0 == x1**

```
    public bool CheckStraightLine(int[][] c) {
        Func<int[], bool> isOnLine;
        if (c[0][0] == c[1][0]) {
            isOnLine = point => point[0] == c[0][0];
        }
        else {
            var a = (c[0][1] - c[1][1]) / (c[0][0] - c[1][0]);
            var b = c[0][1] - a * c[0][0];
            isOnLine = point => point[1] == a * point[0] + b;
        }
        return c.Skip(2).All(isOnLine);
    }
```

2) Another solution I borrowed from [here](https://leetcode.com/problems/check-if-it-is-a-straight-line/discuss/408984/JavaPython-3-check-slopes-short-code-w-explanation-and-analysis.). There is also solution explanation there.
