# Intuition
It is just a Math problem related to slope.

# Approach
If the slope of every two adjacent elements are same, they will lie on the same line.

There is an edge case when the difference of x coordinates is 0 the slope will be undefined so in that case make slope as INT_MAX.

First let us calculate the slope of first two points and continue calculating the next adjacent points. If the slope is same continue else break.

At last if it encounters all the points, the points lie in the same line return true else return false.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(N)

- Space complexity:
O(1)

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    bool checkStraightLine(vector<vector<int>>& coordinates) {
        int n = coordinates.size();
        int i = 1;
        double x = coordinates[1][0] - coordinates[0][0];
        double y = coordinates[1][1] - coordinates[0][1];
        double slope = INT_MAX;
        if(x){
            slope = y/x;
        }
        while(i<n){
            x = coordinates[i][0] - coordinates[i-1][0];
            y = coordinates[i][1] - coordinates[i-1][1];
            double temp = INT_MAX;
            if(x){
                temp = y/x;
            }
            if(temp != slope){
                break;
            }
            i++;
        }
        if(i!=n){
            return 0;
        }
        return 1;
    }
};
```

