# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
For checking if some points are in same straight line, just check the slope of these points, if all the slopes come same then they are definitely in a straight line.
All points in a straight line has the same slope with each other

## **Formlua for slope(m) between two points:**
![slope-formula.png](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/729ab94f-0c85-4954-82a9-d32d5bd1f875_1685932433.1479015.png)


# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(1)
- n = no. of points (coordinates.size())
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    bool checkStraightLine(vector<vector<int>>& coordinates) {
        // if only 2 points, then always straight line
        if(coordinates.size()==2) return true;
        
        // if the points on x axis is an edge case handled here
        if(coordinates[1][0]==0 && coordinates[0][0]==0){
            for(int i=0;i<coordinates.size();i++){
                if(coordinates[i][0]!=0) return false;
            }
            return true;
        }

        //calculate slope then check if all two points lie in same slope
        double slope = (coordinates[1][1] - coordinates[0][1])/double(coordinates[1][0]-coordinates[0][0]);

        for(int i=1;i<coordinates.size();i++){
            double x=(coordinates[i][1] - coordinates[i-1][1])/double(coordinates[i][0]-coordinates[i-1][0]);
            if(x!=slope) return false;
        }
        return true;
    }
};
```

