The slope for a line through any 2 points (x0, y0) and (x1, y1) is  ` (y1 - y0) / (x1 - x0)`
The slope for a line through any 2 points (x1,y1) and (x,y) is ` (y-y1) / (x-x1)`
if these 3 points are in straight line the 2 slopes must be equal;

slope formula

`(y - y1) / (x - x1) = (y1 - y0) / (x1 - x0)`

In multiplication form:

```
(x1 - x0) * (y - y1) = (x - x1) * (y1 - y0) 

a * (y - y1) = b * (x - x1),    where a = x1 - x0 and b = y1 - y0
```



