solutions.content:
If all points in the same line then the slope between any two points should be equal.
So this problem boils down to get slope between two points. 
Suppose we have two slope.

a / b and c / d. 

if (a /b == c /d), then we must have a * d == b * c.

And this is what we need to check for each point.

```
class Solution {
public:
    bool checkStraightLine(vector<vector<int>>& coordinates) {
        int is_straight = true;
        int dy = coordinates[1][1] - coordinates[0][1];
        int dx = coordinates[1][0] - coordinates[0][0];

        for(int i=2; i < coordinates.size(); i++) {
            int cur_dy = coordinates[i][1] - coordinates[i-1][1];
            int cur_dx = coordinates[i][0]- coordinates[i-1][0];

            if(cur_dx * dy != cur_dy * dx) return false;
        }
        return true;
    }
};
```

