Idea: Calculate the vector using the first 2 points. For every other point, calculate the vector from the one of the initial 2 points and check if new vector is parallel to the initial vector using their cross product(done using determinants..hence avoids division). If cross product is not zero...the points are not inline.
```
class Solution {
public:
    bool checkStraightLine(vector<vector<int>>& c) {
        int n = c.size();
        if(n <= 1) return false;
        else if(n==2) return true;
        int dx = c[1][0] - c[0][0], dy = c[1][1] - c[0][1];


