solutions.content:
enumerate each number excluding first and last numbers to be top of mountain.
we can calculate longest increasing sequence from left to right and right to left.
and get the size of moutain array in each position,
if length of lis is 1, it can not be one of side of  moutain array, skip it.

tc is O(nlogn), sc is O(n).

### python
```python
class Solution:
    def minimumMountainRemovals(self, nums: List[int]) -> int:
        size = len(nums)
        lis1 = [0] * size
        lis2 = [0] * size

        piles = []
        for i, x in enumerate(nums):
            if not piles or x > piles[-1]:
                piles.append(x)
                lis1[i] = len(piles)
                continue
            left = bisect.bisect_left(piles, x)
            lis1[i] = left + 1
            piles[left] = x

        piles.clear()
        for i in range(size-1,-1,-1):
            x = nums[i]
            if not piles or x > piles[-1]:
                piles.append(x)
                lis2[i] = len(piles)
                continue
            left = bisect.bisect_left(piles, x)
            lis2[i] = left + 1
            piles[left] = x

        ans = size + 1
        for i in range(1, size-1):
            if lis1[i] == 1 or lis2[i] == 1: continue
            removed = size - (lis1[i] + lis2[i] - 1)
            ans = ans if ans < removed else removed
        return ans
```

