We may use dp to enumerate the first palindromic sequence. Since the maximum length of the original string is only 12 - the iteration goes up to `2**12=4096` times. Actually, small sized problem should always remind you to think about brute force.

After that, just try to find the longest palindromic subsequence in the rest characters. That's a classic problem. You can find the exact same problem here https://leetcode.com/problems/longest-palindromic-subsequence/.
```
class Solution:
    def maxPalindrome(self, s):
        n = len(s)
        dp = [[0] * n for _ in range(n)]
        for i in range(n):
            dp[i][i] = 1
        for i in range(n - 1, -1, -1):
            for j in range(i + 1, n):
                if s[i] == s[j]:
                    dp[i][j] = dp[i+1][j-1]+2
                else:
